The Lagos state Internal Revenue Service, LIRS, has urged Olamilekan Agbeleshe, popularly known ‘Laycon’ who just emerged as the winner of the 2020 edition of the Big Brother Nigeria reality Tv show, to be prepared to pay his tax in 2021. LIRS made this known in a tweet via its Official Twitter account on Monday, while congratulating the reality show winner on his victory. “Congratulations Laycon, winner of BBNaija Lockdown edition. “More wins!! We look forward to seeing you in Y2021 as you pay your tax,”the tweet read. Recall that Laycon emerged the winner of the 2020 edition of the Big Brother Naija reality show on Sunday, after 71 days of participating in the show. He got 60 per cent of the total votes cast by viewers to beat fellow housemate, Dorathy Bachor, who got 21.65 per cent of the votes.<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-844048" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/unnamed-4-1.jpg" alt="" width="1242" height="696" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/unnamed-4-1.jpg 1242w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/unnamed-4-1-300x168.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/unnamed-4-1-1024x574.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px"> 